          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">In a few weeks, I=
=E2=80=99m told, CNN C.E.O. <b>Mark Thompson</b> and his digital lieutenant=
, <b>Alex MacCallum</b>, will unveil to the staff their <i>very </i>long-aw=
aited plan to transform the beleaguered 44-year-old global newsroom into a =
dynamic multiplatform business=E2=80=94one that will ostensibly deepen enga=
gement among CNN=E2=80=99s large but transient online audience, introduce s=
ubscription offerings, and drive new revenue streams. <br/><br/>Needless to=
 say, it can=E2=80=99t come soon enough. Last week, CNN averaged just 485,0=
00 viewers in primetime (roughly equivalent to the Food Network) and <i>88,=
000</i> in the 25-to-54 demo (<i>exactly </i>equal to the Hallmark Channel)=
=2E And while Thompson has long articul=
ated the importance of prioritizing CN=
N=E2=80=99s post-linear future while giving his primetime anchors =E2=80=9C=
time to bed in,=E2=80=9D he no doubt also recognizes that
linear continues to pay the bills=E2=80=94and, presumably, understands that=
 he needs to manage the decline of his television audience in order to buil=
d a runway for growth on streaming and digital.<br/><br/>To that end, Thomp=
son earlier this week announced the news I had reported late last week: <b>=
Charlie Moore</b>, the longtime executive producer for <b>Anderson Cooper</=
b>=E2=80=99s 8 p.m show, will be elevated to vice president of primetime pr=
ogramming, overseeing the hours between 7 p.m. and midnight. His move has l=
ed to all manner of speculation in the newsroom: Is Anderson leaving CNN? (=
No, his contract runs to 2026.) Is he going to scale back to a <b>Maddow</b=
>-style, once-a-week arrangement? (No, he doesn=E2=80=99t have that kind of=
 following.) Is this a bad sign for <b>Erin Burnett </b>and her E.P. <b>Sus=
ie Xu</b>, who have long competed with Anderson and Charlie for bookings an=
d will now ostensibly report to Charlie? (Yes, a little, but Erin=E2=80=99s=
 show isn=E2=80=99t the problem, and
they=E2=80=99ll be fine). <br/><br/>In fact, the Moore promotion signals so=
mething far more simple but also more significant: a recognition on Thompso=
n=E2=80=99s part that the primetime strategy he inherited=E2=80=94and, spec=
ifically, the post-Anderson hours from 9 p.m to midnight=E2=80=94actually <=
i>does </i>matter, and that it <i>really</i> isn=E2=80=99t working and need=
s to be fixed. And, furthermore, that programming chief <b>Eric Sherling </=
b>is too busy with the CNN Max strategy and the election and the upcoming p=
residential debate (the one night that <i>will </i>rate, <i>bigly</i>) to g=
ive those hours the attention they deserve. Whether that portends changes i=
n the lineup or merely a renewed effort to produce the existing talent is T=
=2EB.D.<br/><br/>Meanwhile, one thing I=
 <i>am</i> certain about, unfortunatel=
y, is that there are more cuts coming at CNN. As part of Thompson=E2=80=99s=
 grand transformation, department leaders have been asked to submit names o=
f staffers who might potentially be cut, and
certain areas like digital editorial and international are expected to bear=
 an outsize share of the burden. It=E2=80=99s not clear exactly how many po=
sitions will be cut, and Thompson will likely make the cuts incrementally (=
and quietly) rather than all at once. <br/><br/>Asked about these impending=
 cuts, a CNN spokesperson told me: =E2=80=9CAs Mark outlined this spring, w=
e are undergoing a transformation to ensure CNN remains the global, multipl=
atform leader of news and information across television, digital, and strea=
ming platforms for generations to come. Hundreds of people are involved in =
this process, and no final decisions have been made. Any reports to the con=
trary are inaccurate.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Thompson and MacCallum won=E2=80=99=
t be getting into this sort of nitty-gritty, of course, as they present the=
ir vision. But these moves, uncomfortable as they may be, actually represen=
t meaningful forward momentum. The <b>Licht </b>era (or Licht-<b>Zaz</b>-<b=
>Malone </b>era) was defined by
screwing up stuff that had worked pretty well=E2=80=94moving <b>Don Lemon <=
/b>to the mornings, changing the chyrons, mashing up the morning, etcetera.=
 Now, after quarters of studying the business, Thompson appears ready to re=
ally dig in and correct the mistakes. <br/></td>
